               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">The oldest Mss. (fragments) from the local collection date to the 15th cent.</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Dabr. 
                     Formerly, the church of Mastǝḥ ʾAbuna Libānos existed in the vicinity of Mǝdra Rubā. 
                     According to the local people, some time in 1970s the community decided that it should be merged with the church of Mǝdra Rubā Śǝllase. 
                     Therefore the tābot(s), books and church utensils of Mastǝḥ were moved to Mǝdra Rubā Śǝllāse.
</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">
                     <t:figure>
                        <t:graphic url="Sites/MR.tif">
                           <t:desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</t:desc>
                        </t:graphic>
                     </t:figure> 
                     46 Mss. photographed: <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr001">MR-001</t:ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr002">MR-002</t:ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr003">MR-003</t:ref> "Synaxarion"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr004">MR-004</t:ref> "Liturgical Texts; Prayer of Incense"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr005">MR-005</t:ref> "The Organ of Praise"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr006">MR-006</t:ref> "Prayers"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr007">MR-007</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr008">MR-008</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr009">MR-009</t:ref> "Homily of the Sabbath"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr010">MR-010</t:ref> "The Book of the Matrimony Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr011">MR-011</t:ref> "Acts of the Apostles"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr012">MR-012</t:ref> "Homily of the Sabbath"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr013">MR-013</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr014">MR-014</t:ref> "Vita of John the Baptist"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr014">MR-014</t:ref>b "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr015">MR-015</t:ref> "Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr016">MR-016</t:ref> "Prayer of the Saviour of the World"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr017">MR-017</t:ref> "Prayer of Incense"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr018">MR-018</t:ref> "Book of Mǝʿraf-Hymns"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr019">MR-019</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr020">MR-020</t:ref> "Collection of Miracles of Mary; Jesus and other texts"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr021">MR-021</t:ref> "Psalter"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr022">MR-022</t:ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr023">MR-023</t:ref> "Vita of Cyriacus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr024">MR-024</t:ref> "Book of  ʾAsläṭi"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr025">MR-025</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr026">MR-026</t:ref> "Four Gospels"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr027">MR-027</t:ref> "The Book of the Hours"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr028">MR-028</t:ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr029">MR-029</t:ref> "Miracles of Jesus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr030">MR-030</t:ref> "Collection of homilies"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr031">MR-031</t:ref> "Psalter of the Night"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr032">MR-032</t:ref> "Four Gospels"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr033">MR-033</t:ref> "Four Gospels"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr033">MR-033</t:ref>b "Homily of St. Michael"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr034">MR-034</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr035">MR-035</t:ref> "History of Ethiopia"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr036">MR-036</t:ref> "Vita of Täklä Haymanot"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr037">MR-037</t:ref> "Synaxarion"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr038">MR-038</t:ref> "Vita of Täklä Haymanot"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr039">MR-039</t:ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr040">MR-040</t:ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr041">MR-041</t:ref> "Synaxarion (December)"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr043">MR-043</t:ref> "Story of the Trynity" and different texts"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr045">MR-045</t:ref> "The Faith of the Fathers" and an Amharic treatise.

The library of the church incorporated books from a church dedicated to Libānos (Libānos of Masṭǝḥ), which does not exist any more, as well as the church of 
Dabra Mikāʾel ʾƎnbā Ḥarisāy (the church of the people ʾƎnbā/ʾƎmbā Ḥarisāy/Ḥarišāy), which most probably also does not exist any more.</t:ab>
                 
